{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Feature Engineering: Abstract Structure Features\n",
    "\n",
    "Extract linguistic and structural signals from abstract text — features that TF-IDF\n",
    "cannot capture because it ignores word order, punctuation, and composition.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Hypothesis\n",
    "High-impact papers tend to have:\n",
    "- **Structured abstracts** (explicit IMRaD section headers: Background / Methods / Results / Conclusion)\n",
    "- **Concrete numerical results** (effect sizes, p-values, percentages)\n",
    "- **Review-like language patterns** (systematic review papers are highly cited)\n",
    "- **Specific length profiles** (not too short, not too long)\n",
    "\n",
    "These signals are orthogonal to TF-IDF vocabulary features.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Features Engineered\n",
    "| Feature | Type | Description |\n",
    "|---------|------|-------------|\n",
    "| `abstract_word_count` | numeric | Total word count |\n",
    "| `abstract_sentence_count` | numeric | Total sentence count |\n",
    "| `abstract_avg_sentence_len` | numeric | Mean words per sentence |\n",
    "| `abstract_lexical_diversity` | numeric | Unique words / total words |\n",
    "| `abstract_is_structured` | binary | Has explicit IMRaD section headers |\n",
    "| `abstract_has_background` | binary | Contains background / introduction section |\n",
    "| `abstract_has_methods` | binary | Contains methods / methodology section |\n",
    "| `abstract_has_results` | binary | Contains results / findings section |\n",
    "| `abstract_has_conclusion` | binary | Contains conclusion / discussion section |\n",
    "| `abstract_imrad_score` | numeric | Count of IMRaD sections present (0–4) |\n",
    "| `abstract_has_numbers` | binary | Contains at least one number |\n",
    "| `abstract_number_density` | numeric | Numbers per 100 words |\n",
    "| `abstract_has_pvalue` | binary | Contains a p-value pattern (p<0.05, p=0.03, …) |\n",
    "| `abstract_has_percent` | binary | Contains percentage (e.g. "34%", "34 percent") |\n",
    "| `abstract_has_ci` | binary | Contains confidence interval pattern |\n",
    "| `abstract_has_n_equals` | binary | Contains sample-size pattern (n=123) |\n",
    "| `abstract_question_count` | numeric | Number of question marks (framing questions) |\n",
    "| `abstract_is_missing` | binary | Abstract is missing / empty |\n",
    "\n",
    "## Steps\n",
    "1. Load cleaned data\n",
    "2. Engineer all abstract structure features\n",
    "3. Exploratory analysis — compare high-vs-low impact distributions\n",
    "4. Evaluate standalone with Logistic Regression (5-fold CV)\n",
    "5. Evaluate combined with existing features (text + venue + author)\n",
    "6. Save features"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.append('../')\n",
    "\n",
    "import re\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import StratifiedKFold, cross_validate\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import f1_score, roc_auc_score\n",
    "\n",
    "pd.set_option('display.max_columns', None)\n",
    "RANDOM_STATE = 42"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Load Data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df = pd.read_pickle('../data/processed/cleaned_data.pkl')\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset: {df.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Abstracts present: {df['Abstract'].notna().sum()} / {len(df)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nSample abstract:\\n{str(df['Abstract'].iloc[0])[:400]}...\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Feature Extraction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── IMRaD section-header patterns ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Match common structured-abstract labels that appear as \"Header:\" or \"[Header]\"\n",
    "_BACKGROUND = re.compile(\n",
    "    r'\\b(background|introduction|context|purpose|objective|aim|rationale)\\s*[:\\.]',\n",
    "    re.IGNORECASE\n",
    ")\n",
    "_METHODS = re.compile(\n",
    "    r'\\b(methods?|methodology|design|materials?|procedure|approach|setting)\\s*[:\\.]',\n",
    "    re.IGNORECASE\n",
    ")\n",
    "_RESULTS = re.compile(\n",
    "    r'\\b(results?|findings?|outcomes?|observations?)\\s*[:\\.]',\n",
    "    re.IGNORECASE\n",
    ")\n",
    "_CONCLUSION = re.compile(\n",
    "    r'\\b(conclusions?|discussion|implications?|interpretation|significance)\\s*[:\\.]',\n",
    "    re.IGNORECASE\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Quantitative result patterns ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "_NUMBER   = re.compile(r'\\b\\d+([.,]\\d+)?\\b')\n",
    "_PVALUE   = re.compile(r'p\\s*[<=>≤≥]\\s*0?\\.\\d+', re.IGNORECASE)\n",
    "_PERCENT  = re.compile(r'\\d+([.,]\\d+)?\\s*(%|percent)', re.IGNORECASE)\n",
    "_CI       = re.compile(\n",
    "    r'(95\\s*%?\\s*ci|confidence interval|\\[\\s*\\d+[.,]?\\d*\\s*[,–-]\\s*\\d+[.,]?\\d*\\s*\\])',\n",
    "    re.IGNORECASE\n",
    ")\n",
    "_N_EQUALS = re.compile(r'\\bn\\s*=\\s*\\d+', re.IGNORECASE)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def extract_abstract_features(text):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Return a dict of structural features for a single abstract string.\"\"\"\n",
    "    if pd.isna(text) or str(text).strip() == '':\n",
    "        # Return zero-feature row for missing abstracts\n",
    "        return {\n",
    "            'abstract_word_count': 0,\n",
    "            'abstract_sentence_count': 0,\n",
    "            'abstract_avg_sentence_len': 0.0,\n",
    "            'abstract_lexical_diversity': 0.0,\n",
    "            'abstract_is_structured': 0,\n",
    "            'abstract_has_background': 0,\n",
    "            'abstract_has_methods': 0,\n",
    "            'abstract_has_results': 0,\n",
    "            'abstract_has_conclusion': 0,\n",
    "            'abstract_imrad_score': 0,\n",
    "            'abstract_has_numbers': 0,\n",
    "            'abstract_number_density': 0.0,\n",
    "            'abstract_has_pvalue': 0,\n",
    "            'abstract_has_percent': 0,\n",
    "            'abstract_has_ci': 0,\n",
    "            'abstract_has_n_equals': 0,\n",
    "            'abstract_question_count': 0,\n",
    "            'abstract_is_missing': 1,\n",
    "        }\n",
    "\n",
    "    text = str(text)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Basic counts\n",
    "    words = text.split()\n",
    "    word_count = len(words)\n",
    "    # Split on sentence-ending punctuation\n",
    "    sentences = [s.strip() for s in re.split(r'[.!?]+', text) if s.strip()]\n",
    "    sent_count = max(len(sentences), 1)\n",
    "    avg_sent_len = word_count / sent_count\n",
    "    unique_words = set(w.lower() for w in words if w.isalpha())\n",
    "    alpha_words = [w for w in words if w.isalpha()]\n",
    "    lexical_div = len(unique_words) / max(len(alpha_words), 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # IMRaD flags\n",
    "    has_bg   = int(bool(_BACKGROUND.search(text)))\n",
    "    has_meth = int(bool(_METHODS.search(text)))\n",
    "    has_res  = int(bool(_RESULTS.search(text)))\n",
    "    has_con  = int(bool(_CONCLUSION.search(text)))\n",
    "    imrad    = has_bg + has_meth + has_res + has_con\n",
    "    is_structured = int(imrad >= 2)          # ≥2 explicit labels = structured\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Quantitative result flags\n",
    "    numbers = _NUMBER.findall(text)\n",
    "    has_numbers = int(len(numbers) > 0)\n",
    "    number_density = len(numbers) / word_count * 100 if word_count > 0 else 0.0\n",
    "    has_pvalue  = int(bool(_PVALUE.search(text)))\n",
    "    has_percent = int(bool(_PERCENT.search(text)))\n",
    "    has_ci      = int(bool(_CI.search(text)))\n",
    "    has_n_eq    = int(bool(_N_EQUALS.search(text)))\n",
    "\n",
    "    question_count = text.count('?')\n",
    "\n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        'abstract_word_count':       word_count,\n",
    "        'abstract_sentence_count':   sent_count,\n",
    "        'abstract_avg_sentence_len': avg_sent_len,\n",
    "        'abstract_lexical_diversity': lexical_div,\n",
    "        'abstract_is_structured':    is_structured,\n",
    "        'abstract_has_background':   has_bg,\n",
    "        'abstract_has_methods':      has_meth,\n",
    "        'abstract_has_results':      has_res,\n",
    "        'abstract_has_conclusion':   has_con,\n",
    "        'abstract_imrad_score':      imrad,\n",
    "        'abstract_has_numbers':      has_numbers,\n",
    "        'abstract_number_density':   number_density,\n",
    "        'abstract_has_pvalue':       has_pvalue,\n",
    "        'abstract_has_percent':      has_percent,\n",
    "        'abstract_has_ci':           has_ci,\n",
    "        'abstract_has_n_equals':     has_n_eq,\n",
    "        'abstract_question_count':   question_count,\n",
    "        'abstract_is_missing':       0,\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "struct_df = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "    [extract_abstract_features(t) for t in df['Abstract']],\n",
    "    index=df.index\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Abstract structure features: {struct_df.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nFeature summary:\")\n",
    "print(struct_df.describe().T[['mean', 'std', 'min', 'max']].round(3))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Exploratory Analysis — High vs Low Impact"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Build binary target\n",
    "threshold = df['Citations'].quantile(0.75)\n",
    "y = (df['Citations'] >= threshold).astype(int)\n",
    "print(f\"Top-25% threshold: {threshold:.0f} citations\")\n",
    "print(f\"High-impact: {y.sum()} ({y.mean()*100:.1f}%)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compare means per class\n",
    "struct_df['_label'] = y.values\n",
    "comparison = struct_df.groupby('_label').mean().T\n",
    "comparison.columns = ['Low impact (mean)', 'High impact (mean)']\n",
    "comparison['Ratio (High/Low)'] = comparison['High impact (mean)'] / comparison['Low impact (mean)'].replace(0, np.nan)\n",
    "struct_df.drop(columns='_label', inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nFeature means by class:\")\n",
    "print(comparison.round(3).sort_values('Ratio (High/Low)', ascending=False))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visualise distributions for the most discriminating continuous features\n",
    "plot_features = [\n",
    "    'abstract_word_count', 'abstract_avg_sentence_len',\n",
    "    'abstract_lexical_diversity', 'abstract_number_density'\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 4, figsize=(16, 4))\n",
    "for ax, feat in zip(axes, plot_features):\n",
    "    low  = struct_df.loc[y == 0, feat]\n",
    "    high = struct_df.loc[y == 1, feat]\n",
    "    ax.hist(low,  bins=40, alpha=0.6, color='steelblue', label='Low',  density=True)\n",
    "    ax.hist(high, bins=40, alpha=0.6, color='tomato',    label='High', density=True)\n",
    "    ax.set_title(feat.replace('abstract_', ''), fontsize=9)\n",
    "    ax.legend(fontsize=8)\n",
    "plt.suptitle('Abstract structure features: High vs Low impact', y=1.02)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('../reports/figures/abstract_structure_distributions.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Binary feature rates\n",
    "binary_feats = [\n",
    "    'abstract_is_structured', 'abstract_has_background', 'abstract_has_methods',\n",
    "    'abstract_has_results', 'abstract_has_conclusion', 'abstract_has_pvalue',\n",
    "    'abstract_has_percent', 'abstract_has_ci', 'abstract_has_n_equals', 'abstract_is_missing'\n",
    "]\n",
    "rates = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'Low impact %':  struct_df.loc[y==0, binary_feats].mean() * 100,\n",
    "    'High impact %': struct_df.loc[y==1, binary_feats].mean() * 100,\n",
    "})\n",
    "rates['Lift'] = rates['High impact %'] / rates['Low impact %'].replace(0, np.nan)\n",
    "print(\"\\nBinary feature prevalence by class:\")\n",
    "print(rates.round(2).sort_values('Lift', ascending=False))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Standalone Evaluation (Structure Features Only, 5-fold CV)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-10",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_struct = struct_df.values\n",
    "y_arr    = y.values\n",
    "\n",
    "pipe = Pipeline([\n",
    "    ('scaler', StandardScaler()),\n",
    "    ('lr', LogisticRegression(class_weight='balanced', max_iter=1000,\n",
    "                              random_state=RANDOM_STATE, C=1.0))\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "cv = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=RANDOM_STATE)\n",
    "cv_res = cross_validate(pipe, X_struct, y_arr, cv=cv,\n",
    "                        scoring=['f1', 'roc_auc'], return_train_score=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "f1_struct  = cv_res['test_f1'].mean()\n",
    "auc_struct = cv_res['test_roc_auc'].mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Structure-only LR (5-fold CV):\")\n",
    "print(f\"  F1      : {f1_struct:.4f} ± {cv_res['test_f1'].std():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  ROC-AUC : {auc_struct:.4f} ± {cv_res['test_roc_auc'].std():.4f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-11",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Combined Evaluation (Existing Features + Structure, Temporal Split)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-12",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "feature_dir = Path('../data/features')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load existing feature matrix (best known configuration)\n",
    "X_train_base = pd.read_pickle(feature_dir / 'X_train_temporal.pkl')\n",
    "X_test_base  = pd.read_pickle(feature_dir / 'X_test_temporal.pkl')\n",
    "y_train      = pd.read_pickle(feature_dir / 'y_train_cls_temporal.pkl')\n",
    "y_test       = pd.read_pickle(feature_dir / 'y_test_cls_temporal.pkl')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Existing train features: {X_train_base.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Existing test  features: {X_test_base.shape}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-13",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Align structure features with temporal split\n",
    "train_idx = X_train_base.index\n",
    "test_idx  = X_test_base.index\n",
    "\n",
    "struct_train = struct_df.loc[train_idx]\n",
    "struct_test  = struct_df.loc[test_idx]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Append structure features\n",
    "X_train_aug = pd.concat([X_train_base, struct_train], axis=1)\n",
    "X_test_aug  = pd.concat([X_test_base,  struct_test],  axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Augmented train: {X_train_aug.shape}  (+{struct_train.shape[1]} structure features)\")\n",
    "print(f\"Augmented test : {X_test_aug.shape}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-14",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.metrics import classification_report\n",
    "\n",
    "BASELINE_F1  = 0.6254\n",
    "BASELINE_AUC = 0.8104\n",
    "BASELINE_THR = 0.54\n",
    "\n",
    "def evaluate(X_tr, y_tr, X_te, y_te, threshold=BASELINE_THR, label=''):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Fit LR, predict at given threshold, return F1 and AUC.\"\"\"\n",
    "    lr = LogisticRegression(\n",
    "        class_weight='balanced', max_iter=1000,\n",
    "        random_state=RANDOM_STATE, C=1.0\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    lr.fit(X_tr, y_tr)\n",
    "    proba  = lr.predict_proba(X_te)[:, 1]\n",
    "    preds  = (proba >= threshold).astype(int)\n",
    "    f1  = f1_score(y_te, preds)\n",
    "    auc = roc_auc_score(y_te, proba)\n",
    "    if label:\n",
    "        print(f\"[{label}]  F1={f1:.4f}  AUC={auc:.4f}  threshold={threshold}\")\n",
    "    return f1, auc, lr, proba\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- Baseline (no structure features, same threshold) ---\n",
    "f1_base, auc_base, _, _ = evaluate(\n",
    "    X_train_base, y_train, X_test_base, y_test,\n",
    "    threshold=BASELINE_THR, label='Baseline (existing features)'\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- Augmented (existing + structure features) ---\n",
    "f1_aug, auc_aug, lr_aug, proba_aug = evaluate(\n",
    "    X_train_aug, y_train, X_test_aug, y_test,\n",
    "    threshold=BASELINE_THR, label='Augmented (+ structure features)'\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-15",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# --- Re-optimise threshold on the augmented model ---\n",
    "best_f1, best_thr = 0.0, BASELINE_THR\n",
    "for thr in np.arange(0.30, 0.70, 0.01):\n",
    "    preds = (proba_aug >= thr).astype(int)\n",
    "    f = f1_score(y_test, preds)\n",
    "    if f > best_f1:\n",
    "        best_f1, best_thr = f, thr\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Optimal threshold for augmented model: {best_thr:.2f}  →  F1={best_f1:.4f}\")\n",
    "f1_aug_opt = best_f1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-16",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Results table ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "delta_f1  = f1_aug_opt - BASELINE_F1\n",
    "delta_auc = auc_aug    - BASELINE_AUC\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 62)\n",
    "print(f\"{'Configuration':<32} {'F1':>8} {'ROC-AUC':>9}\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 62)\n",
    "print(f\"{'TF-IDF baseline (reported)':<32} {BASELINE_F1:>8.4f} {BASELINE_AUC:>9.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"{'Structure features only':<32} {f1_struct:>8.4f} {auc_struct:>9.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"{'Baseline + structure (thr=0.54)':<32} {f1_aug:>8.4f} {auc_aug:>9.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"{'Baseline + structure (opt thr)':<32} {f1_aug_opt:>8.4f} {auc_aug:>9.4f}\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 62)\n",
    "print(f\"{'Delta vs TF-IDF baseline':<32} {delta_f1:>+8.4f} {delta_auc:>+9.4f}\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 62)\n",
    "\n",
    "if delta_f1 > 0.005:\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n✓ Structure features IMPROVE F1 by {delta_f1:+.4f} points.\")\n",
    "    print(\"  → Re-run notebook 23 with abstract_structure_features.pkl included.\")\n",
    "elif delta_f1 > -0.005:\n",
    "    print(\"\\n~ Structure features have NEGLIGIBLE impact on F1 (within noise).\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n✗ Structure features HURT F1 by {delta_f1:.4f} points. Do not include.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-17",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Feature Importance (from Augmented Model)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-18",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Extract LR coefficients for structure features only\n",
    "feature_names = list(X_train_aug.columns)\n",
    "struct_feature_names = list(struct_df.columns)\n",
    "\n",
    "coef = lr_aug.coef_[0]\n",
    "struct_indices = [feature_names.index(f) for f in struct_feature_names if f in feature_names]\n",
    "struct_coefs = pd.Series(\n",
    "    coef[struct_indices],\n",
    "    index=struct_feature_names\n",
    ").sort_values(key=abs, ascending=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"LR coefficients for abstract structure features (augmented model):\")\n",
    "print(struct_coefs.round(4).to_string())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Bar chart\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
    "colors = ['tomato' if c > 0 else 'steelblue' for c in struct_coefs]\n",
    "struct_coefs.plot(kind='barh', color=colors, ax=ax)\n",
    "ax.axvline(0, color='black', linewidth=0.8)\n",
